metadata.name: Abstract #3
metadata.description:
Abstract #3 is the first piece in the Abstract Lines collection.

I've been intrigued by abstract art for some time now, however I found myself afraid to create an abstract piece for an equally long time.

After visiting Miami for Art Basel, I found myself inspired and wanting to experiment more with my art - which meant it was finally time to try abstract work!

I wanted to call attention to the 3D space of this piece through the use of contrasting shapes, colors, and angles.

It leaves me feeling retro, happy, Miami vibes - I hope it does the same for you!
